{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Calls the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"method"},{"type":"text","text":" on the object during idle time. Always returns null, "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"not","type":"text"}]},{"text":" the method’s result.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"callDeferred"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"method"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/StringName","text":"StringName","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot10StringNameC","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"arguments"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7VariantC","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","text":"Variant"},{"kind":"text","text":"...) -> "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Variant","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7VariantC"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Idle time happens mainly at the end of process and physics frames. In it, deferred calls will be run until there are none left, which means you can defer calls from other deferred calls and they’ll still be run in the current idle time cycle. If not done carefully, this can result in infinite recursion without causing a stack overflow, which will hang the game similarly to an infinite loop.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method supports a variable number of arguments, so parameters can be passed as a comma separated list."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See also ","type":"text"},{"code":"Callable\/callDeferred()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In C#, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"method"},{"text":" must be in snake_case when referring to built-in Godot methods. Prefer using the names exposed in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MethodName"},{"text":" class to avoid allocating a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/StringName","isActive":true},{"text":" on each call.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re looking to delay the function call by a frame, refer to the [signal SceneTree.process_frame] and [signal SceneTree.physics_frame] signals.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/object\/calldeferred(method:_:)"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6ObjectC12callDeferred6method_AA7VariantCAA10StringNameC_AGdtF","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"symbol","title":"callDeferred(method:_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"callDeferred","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"method","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot10StringNameC","text":"StringName"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Variant","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7VariantC"},{"text":"...) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Variant","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7VariantC","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"roleHeading":"In